dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset represents the SEQ Regional Plan 2009-2031 Regional Landuse Categories, composed of three land use categories: 1) Regional Landscape and Rural Production Area 2) Urban Footprint 3) Rural Living Area The dataset is produced from the Digital Cadastral Database (DCDB) March 2009, sourced from Department of Environment and Resource Management. This includes property parcels, road, railway and watercourse boundaries. Based on the existing Draft South East Queensland Regional Plan 2009-2031 - December 2008, with supported submissions including current planning scheme intents, forward planning designations, and advice from local government and state government agencies.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The purpose of the South East Queensland Regional Plan 2009â€“2031 (SEQ Regional Plan) is to manage regional growth and change in the most sustainable way to protect and enhance quality of life in the region. This Dataset represents the core land use categories in the Plan.

prcStep.stepDesc: The RLUC layers (the urban footprint etc) from the Draft Regional Plan were used as the base attribute layer. This Layer was then shifted to the March 2009 DCDB based on adjusted centroid elements of the DCDB land parcels. Attributes from the Draft SEQ RLUC layer were transposed into a new layer with the positional accuracy and attribute information from a composite version of the March 2009 DCDB. The method of transposition is based on adjusted centroid elements of the DCDB land parcels. This allows for minor source data projection shifts due to slight differences in the DCDB. Generic underlying attribute information are also recorded at this stage. Feature Dataset topology within ESRI 9.2 geodatabase was created and all new edits & changes (Major Planning Designation Changes) were accommodated at this time. Issues with the dataset's topological accuracy and accuracy relative to the March 2009 DCDB parcels were corrected using ESRI topology error inspector in ESRI Arc-Info. Small errors such as slithers and incorrect node consistancy were corrceted using the error inspector. All features were then subjected to a strict validation and QA check inside the topology. The final geospatial topology model was exported to ESRI shape format for distribution. Positional and parcel boundary information primarily sourced from the March 2009 DCDB - Cadastre. Additional Planning information sourced from local and state government agencies, and the Draft SEQ Regional Plan 2009-2031, (December 2008).
